COMPLETION REPORT
AGENT: codex
TASK: Implemented Phase 10 HTTP API handlers and route wiring for internal/web
DATE: 2026-03-05
STATUS: partial

## Files Changed
- created: internal/web/handler/handler.go
- created: internal/web/handler/general.go
- created: internal/web/handler/config.go
- created: internal/web/handler/printer.go
- created: internal/web/handler/notifications.go
- created: internal/web/handler/settings.go
- created: internal/web/handler/history.go
- created: internal/web/handler/timelapse.go
- created: internal/web/handler/filament.go
- created: internal/web/handler/selector.go
- created: internal/web/handler/slicer.go
- created: internal/web/handler/debug.go
- created: internal/web/handler/bedlevel.go
- created: internal/web/handler/handler_test.go
- modified: internal/web/routes.go
- modified: internal/web/server.go
- modified: internal/web/server_test.go
- modified: internal/service/mqttqueue.go
- modified: internal/service/manager.go

## Decisions Made
- Added a shared "'`handler.Handler` dependency container with consistent JSON/error helpers.
- Wired all Phase-10 routes in `routes.go` to dedicated handler methods and kept WS endpoints as explicit Phase-11 stubs.
- Extended `service.MqttQueue` with API-facing methods (`SendGCode`, `SendAutoLeveling`, `SetLight`, `IsPrinting`, `SnapshotState`, etc.) to avoid handlers reaching into internals.
- Extended `service.ServiceManager` with snapshot/get/restart helpers required by debug and reload endpoints.
- Implemented path traversal protections in timelapse and debug-log endpoints using basename/`..` checks plus absolute-path prefix validation for logs.

## Deviations from Spec
- Several endpoints are intentionally best-effort placeholders and return `501` or simplified behavior:
  - `/video` (still not implemented)
  - `/api/ankerctl/config/login` (httpapi login not wired yet)
  - `/api/printer/bed-leveling` and `/api/printer/bed-leveling/last`
- Root endpoint `/` currently serves a minimal HTML placeholder rather than full template rendering.
- Response compatibility is not yet 1:1 with Python for all routes (core required shapes implemented for `/api/health`, `/api/version`, `/api/history`, filament list).

## Known Issues / TODO
- Integrate real cloud login flow in `internal/httpapi` and connect it to `/api/ankerctl/config/login`.
- Implement `/video` streaming and `/api/snapshot` parity with Python ffmpeg flow/auth behavior.
- Implement bed-leveling live query + persisted last grid endpoint.
- Align remaining response payloads/status codes exactly with Python where still simplified.

## Open Questions for Review
- Should `/api/timelapse/{filename}` keep `Content-Disposition: attachment` (per task) or match Python’s inline behavior?
- Should debug route gating be only route-level (current) or also hard-fail at handler-level for defense in depth?

## Test Coverage
- covered: route wiring smoke paths, `/api/health` and `/api/version`, history response shape key, traversal rejection for timelapse and debug logs, middleware tests unchanged.
- not covered: real service integration paths (MQTT/PPPP/video/file transfer), cloud login, websocket handlers, full Python response parity validation.
